Africa’s biggest pay-TV business Multichoice intends to pay a R2.5 billion ($181 million) dividend in 2020 after it has been unbundled from its parent, Naspers, its chief financial officer said on Monday. “The board intends to declare an inaugural dividend of R2.5 billion for our financial year 2020,” Tim Jacobs told Reuters by phone, after Multichoice gained approval to list on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange. ($1 = 13.8100 rand)